  "asset": "NQ1!",
  "timeframe": "5M",
  "market_context": "NQ 5-minute chart on 8/11/2023 just before the New York open. Price had been grinding higher overnight with buy-side liquidity resting above old highs near 15412. Midnight open (0:00) sat near 15358 and London lows rested below as the next downside draw.",
  "key_observation": "After price displaced up to sweep buy-side liquidity above the old highs, the first attempt failed to produce a CISD, but a second sweep was followed by a close below the series of up-close candles that made the new high, validating the change in state of delivery.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Marked the buy-side liquidity resting above the old highs on the NQ 5-minute chart.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to the 5-minute time frame just before New York open and observed price displace up over the high and back into the range.",
    "Step 3: Identified the series of up-close candles that made the new high and looked for a close below their opening price as the CISD trigger.",
    "Step 4: Noted the first attempt failed to close below, then a second sweep occurred followed by a valid close below the up-close candles, confirming the CISD.",
    "Step 5: Set London lows below as the downside draw on liquidity and planned a retest of the order block with stop on the high.",
    "Step 6: Since target was only 1.66R, applied standard deviation projection on the manipulation leg to extend to the -2 level for a minimum 2R setup.",
    "Step 7: Watched price tag the order block, respect the fair value gap inside it, then close below the entry candle validating it as an order block."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade validated — price tagged the order block, respected the internal FVG, and closed below the entry candle confirming the short setup toward London lows with -2 standard deviation as target.",
  "lessons": "A valid CISD requires a close through the opening price of the up-close candle(s) that made the new high. Combining CISD with standard deviation projections of the manipulation leg allows the trader to extend insufficient R:R setups to a minimum 2R target.",
